cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about visualizing learned features in Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the analysis of why a network might fail for certain examples, which could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) or neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a library for visualizing CNNs, which could be considered as an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) tool.
